'''博尔顿机场''' （{{lang-en|Bolton Field}}，{{Airport codes||KTZR|TZR}}）是美国[[俄亥俄州|俄亥俄州]][[富兰克林县_(俄亥俄州)|富兰克林县]][[哥伦布_(俄亥俄州)|哥伦布]]西南的一座机场，<ref name=FAA />由[[哥伦布地区机场管理局|哥伦布地区机场管理局]]运营，是[[哥伦布国际机场|哥伦布国际机场]]的备用机场。

大多数美国机场的[[美国联邦航空局|FAA]]和[[国际航空运输协会机场代码|IATA]]代码使用的是相同的三个字母，但是博尔顿机场却只有FAA代码'''TZR'''。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://gc.kls2.com/airport/KTZR |title=Great Circle Mapper: KTZR - Columbus, Ohio (Bolton Field) |access-date=2014-11-20 |archive-date=2020-07-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200703024201/http://gc.kls2.com/airport/KTZR |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==历史==
博尔顿机场于1970年10月24日开放，机场以哥伦布国际机场主管弗朗西斯·博尔顿的名字命名，纪念他生前为哥伦布航空做出的长期贡献。该机场为私人和商务航空而建，并且是哥伦布空港的备用机场。1980年，哥伦布空港和博尔顿机场被移交给哥伦布市的哥伦布机场管理局运营，2003年，哥伦布机场管理局和里肯巴克空港管理局合并为哥伦布地区机场管理局。<ref name="Columbus Regional Airport Authority">{{cite web|url=http://columbusairports.com/about-us/our-history/|title=哥伦布地区机场管理局 - 历史|publisher=哥伦布地区机场管理局|accessdate=2014-11-20|archive-date=2011-02-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110207053012/http://columbusairports.com/about-us/our-history/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="The Columbus Dispatch">{{cite web|url=http://www.dispatch.com/content/stories/local/2012/10/24/bolton-field-takes-pressure-off-port-columbus.html|title=Columbus Mileposts: Oct. 24, 1970 Bolton Field takes pressure off Port Columbus|publisher=The Columbus Dispatch|access-date=2014-11-20|archive-date=2020-07-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200703024327/https://www.dispatch.com/content/stories/local/2012/10/24/bolton-field-takes-pressure-off-port-columbus.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 设施和飞机==

===设施===
博尔顿机场占地{{convert|1500|acre|ha|0}}，有一条[[柏油|柏油]][[跑道|跑道]] (4/22) 5,500 x 100 ft (1,676 x 30 m)。<ref name=FAA />机场提供燃油服务，并有[[机库|机库]]和停机坪供飞机停放。

首府喷气机（Capital City Jet）在此机场提供飞行教学<ref name="Capital City Jet Center">{{cite web|url=http://www.capitalcityjet.com/|title=Capital City Jet Center-FBO Services|publisher=Capital City Jet Center|access-date=2014-11-20|archive-date=2020-11-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201126233931/http://www.capitalcityjet.com/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，{{tsl|en|Columbus State Community College|哥伦布州立社区大学}}则在此设有飞机维护训练项目<ref name="Columbus State Community College">{{cite web|url=http://www.cscc.edu/academics/departments/aviation-maintenance/|title=Columbus State Community College-Aviation Maintenance|publisher=Columbus State Community College|access-date=2014-11-20|archive-date=2020-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200810082738/https://www.cscc.edu/academics/departments/aviation-maintenance/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。机场另有 Scioto Valley 99s和俄亥俄热气球俱乐部（Ohio Balloon Club）两家航空组织。<ref name="Scioto Valley 99s">{{cite web|url=http://www.99s-sciotovalley.org/|title=Scioto Valley 99s|publisher=Scioto Valley 99s|access-date=2014-11-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141025132837/http://www.99s-sciotovalley.org/|archive-date=2014-10-25|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name="Central Ohio Balloon Club">{{cite web|url=http://www.centralohioballoonclub.org/|title=Central Ohio Balloon Club-About Us|publisher=Central Ohio Balloon Club|access-date=2014-11-20|archive-date=2019-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190127101208/http://www.centralohioballoonclub.org/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

===飞机===
2011年6月21日之前的一年里，该机场起降架次为74,511次，平均每日204次。其中99%为[[通用航空|通用航空]]，另有不足1%的空中的士和军用飞机。有82架飞机以博尔顿机场为基地，其中90%为单发螺旋桨飞机，6%为多发螺旋桨飞机，2%为喷气机以及1%的[[直升机|直升机]]。<ref name=FAA />

== 事故 ==
* On June 18, 1993, upon approach for landing on Grass Runway 22, a {{tsl|en|Glasflügel H-101}} glider registered N101AZ, encountered a powered airplane, which had entered the landing pattern. The pilot extended his base leg to the approach to accommodate the aircraft. He then decided that it would be difficult to complete the landing on the planned runway, so he switched to a site he was unfamiliar with. During this landing, the glider impacted a ditch. The ultra-light aircraft suffered damage to its tail section.<ref name="AircraftOne.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.aircraftone.com/aircraft/accidents/20001211X12701.asp|title=Aircraft Incident/Accident Report Bolton Field Airport Columbus, Ohio 43228 Friday, June 18, 1993 2:00 PM EDT|publisher=National Transportation Security Board|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130614072435/http://www.aircraftone.com/aircraft/accidents/20001211X12701.asp|archivedate=2013年6月14日|accessdate=2014年11月20日}}</ref>

